Upstream candidate: the OGRE_RESOURCEMANAGER_STRICT=0 fallback lookup in
ZipArchive::open calls zip_entry_open with three arguments, but the bundled
zip library's zip_entry_open takes two (the case-sensitive variant is the
separate zip_entry_opencasesensitive). The branch is preprocessed out in
strict builds, so only non-strict configurations ever compile it - and they
fail. Inside this #else branch OGRE_RESOURCEMANAGER_STRICT is 0 by
definition, so the two-argument (case-insensitive) call preserves the
intended behavior exactly.
--- a/OgreMain/src/OgreZip.cpp
+++ b/OgreMain/src/OgreZip.cpp
@@ -173,7 +173,7 @@ namespace {
             {
                 Ogre::FileInfo info = fileNfo->at(0);
                 lookUpFileName = info.path + info.basename;
-                open = zip_entry_open(mZipFile, lookUpFileName.c_str(), OGRE_RESOURCEMANAGER_STRICT) == 0;
+                open = zip_entry_open(mZipFile, lookUpFileName.c_str()) == 0;
             }
         }
 #endif
